(1. Introduction To The Topic) Tj
T*
(Build websites using HTML, CSS and JavaScript. In a textbook lesson, the first goal is) Tj
T*
(to make the computing concept clear. Students should be able to explain what Web) Tj
T*
(Development means, identify where it appears in Computer Science, and describe the main) Tj
T*
(purpose of the topic without relying on memorized sentences.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. Core Teaching) Tj
T*
(The central focus in Web Development is the main ideas and methods involved in Web) Tj
T*
(Development. This means students must move beyond the overview and understand how the) Tj
T*
(idea actually works. A strong explanation should unpack the rules, relationships, or) Tj
T*
(patterns behind Web Development and show how those ideas guide correct answers. In) Tj
T*
(Computer Science, success usually depends on understanding the commands, structure, and) Tj
T*
(logic that belong to the topic.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. How The Idea Is Applied) Tj
T*
(A useful way to teach Web Development is to connect the explanation directly to a simple) Tj
T*
(classroom example involving Web Development. That kind of system or code example shows) Tj
T*
(students how the topic moves from theory into use. At this stage, the learner should be) Tj
T*
(able to state the relevant rule or principle, explain why it fits the question, and then) Tj
T*
(apply the logical procedure with confidence.) Tj
T*
() Tj
